<br>
Canadian officials released a report recommending the legalization of marijuana.<br>
<br>
The proposal would make it legal for anyone 16 years old or older to buy, use and grow marijuana for personal use.<br>
<br>
In the report, a panel of lawmakers recommended the Canadian government regulate sales and production of marijuana, similar to the way cigarettes and beer are controlled.<br>
<br>
Canadian officials are expected to vote on the proposal some time next year.<br>
